[2;36m                    [0m         [39m@@ [0m[1;36m-115[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m6[0m[39m +[0m[1;36m119[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m41[0m[39m @@[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return [0m[1;35msb.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m [0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     * Sanitizes an embedded path to prevent path traversal attacks.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     * Removes all [0m[32m"."[0m[39m, [0m[32m".."[0m[39m, and empty path components.[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     *[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     * @param path the embedded path to sanitize[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     * @return sanitized path with only safe components[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    private String [0m[1;35msanitizeEmbeddedPath[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath == null || [0m[1;35mpath.isEmpty[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            return [0m[32m""[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Split by both forward and backward slashes[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        String[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m parts = [0m[1;35mpath.split[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"[0m[32m[[0m[32m/\\\\[0m[32m][0m[32m+"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        StringBuilder sanitized = new [0m[1;35mStringBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mString part : parts[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Skip empty parts, [0m[32m"."[0m[39m, and [0m[32m".."[0m[39m to prevent traversal[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mpart.isEmpty[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;35mpart.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"."[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;35mpart.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m".."[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                continue;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Use FilenameUtils.normalize to sanitize reserved characters[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            String normalizedPart = [0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpart[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mnormalizedPart.isEmpty[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35msanitized.length[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                    [0m[1;35msanitized.append[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"/"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA critical security issue has been detected involving file path traversal [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerability in Apache Tika's file system operations. The fuzzer identified that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalicious file paths containing traversal sequences [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `..[0m[35m/[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m can escape [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintended directory boundaries when processing archive files with the [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRUnpackExtractor, potentially allowing unauthorized access to files outside the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdesignated output directory.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe issue manifests as a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` exception with the message [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"File path traversal"[0m[39m when processing a specially crafted input file. The [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerability is triggered during the extraction and emission of embedded documents[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrom archive files.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Vulnerability Type[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis is a **Path Traversal** [0m[1;39m([0m[39malso known as Directory Traversal[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m vulnerability, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclassified as a critical security issue. The detected path shows an attempt to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtraverse outside the intended directory structure using relative path components [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`..[0m[35m/[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in the file path: [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[35m/tmp/expander-tmp5981020633749208628/output/q/r/s/t/./input.bin/../../../[0m[95mjazzer-tr[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [95maversal[0m[39m`.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Key Observations[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Attack Vector**: The vulnerability is exploited through embedded file names [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithin archive files being processed by the RUnpackExtractor. The malicious path [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontains both legitimate directory components and traversal sequences designed to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mescape the output directory.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Detection Point**: The security sanitizer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`FilePathTraversal.check`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msuccessfully detected the traversal attempt at the file system emission stage, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreventing the actual exploitation.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Execution Flow**: The vulnerability surfaces through the following execution [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Archive parsing begins with PackageParser[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - RUnpackExtractor processes embedded documents with byte handling[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - EmittingEmbeddedDocumentBytesHandler attempts to emit extracted content[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - FileSystemEmitter tries to write files to the file system[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Path traversal sanitizer detects the malicious path[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Components Requiring Investigation[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo gain a holistic understanding of this vulnerability, the following codebase [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mareas should be examined:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **FileSystemEmitter** [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`org.apache.tika.pipes.emitter.fs.FileSystemEmitter`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Line [0m[1;36m155[0m[39m where the emission occurs[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Path construction and validation logic[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How file names from embedded documents are handled[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **RUnpackExtractor** [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`org.apache.tika.extractor.RUnpackExtractor`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Methods `storeEmbeddedBytes` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m153[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and `parseWithBytes` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m122[0m[1;39m)[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How embedded file names are extracted and passed downstream[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any existing path sanitization or validation[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **EmittingEmbeddedDocumentBytesHandler** [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`org.apache.tika.pipes.extractor.EmittingEmbeddedDocumentBytesHandler`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `add` method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m66[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that bridges extraction and emission[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Metadata and path information handling for embedded documents[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **PackageParser** [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`org.apache.tika.parser.pkg.PackageParser`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Methods `parseEntry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m481[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and `parseEntries` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m386[0m[1;39m)[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How entry names from archives are processed and propagated[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any existing validation of archive entry paths[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Path Validation Logic**:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Current implementation of path sanitization across the emission pipeline[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Where and how file paths are constructed from archive entry names[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Validation mechanisms before file system operations[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability indicates that untrusted file names from archive entries are [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbeing used to construct output file paths without sufficient validation, allowing [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath traversal sequences to bypass directory restrictions.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m19[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m20[0m[39m: * Contains a core set of basic Tika metadata properties, which all parsers[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m21[0m[39m: * will attempt to supply [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhere the file format permits[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. These are all[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m22[0m[39m: * defined in terms of other standard namespaces.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m23[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m24[0m[39m: * Users of Tika who wish to have consistent metadata across file formats[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m25[0m[39m: * can make use of these Properties, knowing that where present they will[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m26[0m[39m: * have consistent semantic meaning between different file formats. [0m[1;39m([0m[39mNo[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m27[0m[39m: * matter if one file format calls it Title, another Long-Title and another[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m28[0m[39m: * Long-Name, if they all mean the same thing as defined by[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m29[0m[39m: * [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link DublinCore#TITLE[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m then they will all be present as such[0m[1;39m)[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m30[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m31[0m[39m: * For now, most of these properties are composite ones including the deprecated[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m32[0m[39m: * non-prefixed String properties from the Metadata class. In Tika [0m[1;36m2.0[0m[39m, most[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m33[0m[39m: * of these will revert back to simple assignments.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m34[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m35[0m[39m: * @since Apache Tika [0m[1;36m1.2[0m                                                        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m90[0m[39m:     * bad things could happen.  Consider: [0m[32m"../../../my_ppt.ppt"[0m[39m.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m91[0m[39m:     * <p>[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m92[0m[39m:     * Consider using this in combination with [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link #[0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m93[0m[39m:     *[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m98[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m99[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath == null || [0m[1;35mpath.isEmpty[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m100[0m[39m:            return StringUtils.EMPTY;[0m                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m102[0m[39m:        int unix = [0m[1;35mpath.lastIndexOf[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"/"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m103[0m[39m:        int windows = [0m[1;35mpath.lastIndexOf[0m[1;39m([0m[39m"\\"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m104[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95msome[0m[39m macintosh file names are stored with : as the delimiter[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m105[0m[39m:        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95malso[0m[39m necessary to properly handle C:somefilename[0m                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis Summary[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter analyzing the code snippets and the evaluation report, I've identified the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mroot cause and optimal fix strategy for this path traversal vulnerability.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Root Cause[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability exists in a chain of trust violations:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Entry Point [0m[1;39m([0m[39mPackageParser.jav[0m[1;92ma:222[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m223[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: Archive entry names from untrusted[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msources are stored directly in metadata without sanitization[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Path Construction [0m[1;39m([0m[39mAbstractEmbeddedDocumentBytesHandler.jav[0m[1;92ma:77[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m115[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: The [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35membeddedPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method attempts insufficient sanitization via `[0m[1;35maddSubDirs[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mreplaceAll[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"\\.\\./"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"/"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` only removes literal `..[0m[35m/[0m[39m` patterns but doesn't [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevent all traversal forms[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Emission Point [0m[1;39m([0m[39mFileSystemEmitter.jav[0m[1;92ma:147[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m**: The `[0m[1;35memit[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method resolves [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths against `basePath` but **lacks validation** to ensure the resolved path stays[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithin the base directory[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe codebase already contains:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Explicit warnings** in TikaCoreProperties documentation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m58[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m60[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m80[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m82[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39magainst using embedded resource paths for file system operations[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Reference implementation** in FileSystemFetcher [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m78[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m82[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m showing the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorrect validation pattern[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Utility methods** in FilenameUtils for safe filename extraction[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Fix Strategy[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mI'll implement a **defense-in-depth approach** with validation at multiple layers:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Primary Fix: Add Path Traversal Validation in FileSystemEmitter[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tika-pipes/tika-emitters/tika-emitter-fs/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/pipes/emitt[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mer/fs/FileSystemEmitter.java`[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Implementation** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m146[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m151[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. After resolving the path at line [0m[1;36m147[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Path target = [0m[1;35mbasePath.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madd validation **before** line [0m[1;36m149[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Use the same security pattern from [0m[1;35mFileSystemFetcher.fetch[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m78[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m82[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Validate that the resolved path stays within basePath[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mtarget.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mbasePath.toRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Emit path must resolve to be a descendant of the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m'basePath': "[0m[39m + path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Rationale**:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` resolves symbolic links and normalizes the path [0m[1;39m([0m[39mremoves `.` and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`..`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mstartsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` checks if the resolved path is a descendant of basePath[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This mirrors the proven security pattern already used in FileSystemFetcher[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Throws IOException [0m[1;39m([0m[39mconsistent with the method signature[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to prevent emission [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moutside basePath[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Error Handling**:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Wrap the `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` calls in try-catch for IOException [0m[1;39m([0m[39mif files don't exist [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39myet[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In the catch block, use `[0m[1;35mtoAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` as fallback [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlike [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mFileSystemFetcher.isDescendant[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Still validate with `[0m[1;35mstartsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to prevent traversal[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Secondary Fix: Improve Sanitization in AbstractEmbeddedDocumentBytesHandler[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/extractor/AbstractEmbeddedDocumentBytesHan[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdler.java`[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Implementation** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m74[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m91[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImprove the `[0m[1;35membeddedPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method to use FilenameUtils for safer path [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstruction:[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. At line [0m[1;36m77[0m[39m, after retrieving `embeddedPath`, sanitize it:[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   String embeddedPath = [0m[1;35mmetadata.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTikaCoreProperties.RESOURCE_NAME_KEY[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Sanitize the path to extract only the filename components[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39membeddedPath != null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       embeddedPath = [0m[1;35msanitizeEmbeddedPath[0m[1;39m([0m[39membeddedPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Add a new private method `[0m[1;35msanitizeEmbeddedPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```java[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   private String [0m[1;35msanitizeEmbeddedPath[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath == null || [0m[1;35mpath.isEmpty[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           return [0m[32m""[0m[39m;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Split by path separators and sanitize each component[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       String[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m parts = [0m[1;35mpath.split[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"[0m[32m[[0m[32m/\\\\[0m[32m][0m[32m+"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       StringBuilder sanitized = new [0m[1;35mStringBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mString part : parts[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Skip empty parts, [0m[32m"."[0m[39m, and [0m[32m".."[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mpart.isEmpty[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;35mpart.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"."[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;35mpart.equals[0m[1;39m([0m[32m".."[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               continue;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Use FilenameUtils.normalize to sanitize reserved characters[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           String normalizedPart = [0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpart[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mnormalizedPart.isEmpty[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35msanitized.length[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   [0m[1;35msanitized.append[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"/"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m               [0m[1;35msanitized.append[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnormalizedPart[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return [0m[1;35msanitized.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Rationale**:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Removes all path traversal sequences [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`.`, `..`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Uses [0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to handle reserved characters[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Reconstructs a clean path from validated components[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This is a defense-in-depth measure that complements the primary fix[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Tertiary Fix: Validate in PackageParser [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOptional but Recommended[0m[1;39m)[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Location**: [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tika-parsers/tika-parsers-standard/tika-parsers-standard-modules/tika-parser-pkg-m[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39module/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/parser/pkg/PackageParser.java`[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Implementation** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m221[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m223[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdd sanitization when setting the resource name:[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mname != null && [0m[1;35mname.length[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    name = [0m[1;35mname.replace[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"\\", "[0m[35m/[0m[39m"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Extract just the filename to prevent path traversal[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    String safeName = [0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[39mname[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35msafeName.isEmpty[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m If getName returns empty [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., for [0m[32m".."[0m[39m or [0m[32m"."[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, use the full name[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m but log a warning[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        safeName = name;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mLOGGER.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Suspicious archive entry name detected: [0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m"[0m[39m, name[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mentrydata.set[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTikaCoreProperties.RESOURCE_NAME_KEY, safeName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m[39m rest of the code[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Rationale**:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Prevents malicious paths from entering the metadata at the source[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Uses [0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m as recommended in its own documentation[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Logs warnings for suspicious entry names[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Still preserves the entry name for informational purposes[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Critical Implementation Notes[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Never modify harness code** - All fixes target source code only [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mFileSystemEmitter, AbstractEmbeddedDocumentBytesHandler, PackageParser[0m[1;39m)[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Preserve existing functionality**:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Valid embedded paths within basePath continue to work[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing tests should pass[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Only malicious traversal attempts are blocked[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Error handling**:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - IOException is appropriate for FileSystemEmitter [0m[1;39m([0m[39malready in method signature[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Clear error messages help debugging legitimate issues[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Log warnings for suspicious patterns[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Backward compatibility**:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - PATH_STRATEGY.ID [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m already safe, unaffected[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - PATH_STRATEGY.EMBEDDED_PATH becomes safe with these fixes[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing valid use cases continue working[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **No removal of functionality**:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All path strategies still supported[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Archive processing continues normally[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Only security-violating paths are rejected[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This Is Optimal[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Follows existing patterns**: Reuses the proven FileSystemFetcher validation [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapproach[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Defense-in-depth**: Multiple layers of validation [0m[1;39m([0m[39memission, path [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstruction, entry parsing[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Minimal changes**: Focused fixes without restructuring the codebase[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Well-documented**: Uses utilities [0m[1;39m([0m[39mFilenameUtils[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m explicitly designed for this[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpurpose[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Testable**: Clear validation logic that can be unit tested[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **No external dependencies**: Uses only existing Tika utilities[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **Preserves functionality**: Legitimate embedded paths continue working[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Legitimate deeply nested paths might be affected**:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mitigation: The validation only blocks paths that escape basePath[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Paths within basePath [0m[1;39m([0m[39meven deeply nested[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m work correctly[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Symbolic links in embedded paths**:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mitigation: `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` resolves symlinks, preventing symlink-based [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtraversal[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fallback to `[0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` if `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` fails[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Performance impact**:[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mitigation: Path validation is fast [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnative Java NIO operations[0m[1;39m)[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Only occurs once per emitted file[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Error messages for legitimate edge cases**:[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mitigation: Clear error messages help users understand what's blocked[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Logging helps diagnose unexpected blocks[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
