[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a path traversal security vulnerability [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mcom.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m detected during [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzing of the Apache Tika codebase. The vulnerability occurs when processing [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39membedded files within archive formats, where a malicious path containing traversal [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msequences [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`..[0m[35m/[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is used to write files outside the intended output directory. The[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch attempt aimed to sanitize embedded file paths and validate output paths, but [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfailed to compile due to a missing `Initializable` interface reference in the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FileSystemEmitter` class.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue Analysis[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe stack trace reveals a file path traversal vulnerability with the following [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcharacteristics:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Vulnerability Location**: The security issue is triggered at [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mFileSystemEmitter.emit[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` line [0m[1;36m155[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Malicious Path**: [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[35m/tmp/expander-tmp5981020633749208628/output/q/r/s/t/./input.bin/../../../[0m[95mjazzer-tr[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [95maversal[0m[39m`[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Attack Vector**: The path contains traversal components [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`.[0m[35m/[0m[39m` and `..[0m[35m/[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallow escaping the intended output directory[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Call Chain**:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Archive parsing begins with `[0m[1;35mPackageParser.parse[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Embedded documents are extracted via `[0m[1;35mRUnpackExtractor.parseEmbedded[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Embedded bytes are handled by `[0m[1;35mEmittingEmbeddedDocumentBytesHandler.add[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Finally, files are emitted through `[0m[1;35mFileSystemEmitter.emit[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` where the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtraversal occurs[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability exists because embedded file names from untrusted archive [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontents are used directly to construct output file paths without proper validation[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39magainst path traversal attacks.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt Description[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch attempted to fix the vulnerability through two main modifications:[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. FileSystemEmitter.java modifications:**[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Added SLF4J Logger import for logging[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Declared the class as implementing `Initializable` interface [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m71[0m[1;39m)[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Changed `basePath` field from `null` initialization to uninitialized[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Added path traversal validation in the `[0m[1;35memit[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method at line [0m[1;36m152[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m157[0m[39m:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - After resolving the target path, validates that it stays within `basePath`[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Throws `IOException` if the resolved path is not a descendant of `basePath`[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Introduced a new `[0m[1;35misDescendant[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m177[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m194[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that:[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Uses `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to resolve symbolic links and normalize paths[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Validates the descendant path starts with the root path[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Falls back to `[0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` if `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` fails [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., when file doesn't [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexist yet[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**[0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. AbstractEmbeddedDocumentBytesHandler.java modifications:**[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Added path sanitization in the `[0m[1;35mbuildEmitKey[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method at lines [0m[1;36m78[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m81[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Introduced a new `[0m[1;35msanitizeEmbeddedPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m122[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m154[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that:[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Splits paths by forward and backward slashes[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Filters out empty parts, `.`, and `..` components[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Uses `[0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` for additional sanitization[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Reconstructs the path using only safe components[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Compilation Error[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch failed to compile with the following error:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m[[0m[39mERROR[0m[1;39m][0m[39m [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/project-parent/tika/tika-pipes/tika-emitters/tika-emitter-fs/src/main/java/org[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/apache/tika/pipes/emitter/fs/[0m[95mFileSystemEmitter.java[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m71[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m82[0m[1;39m][0m[39m cannot find symbol[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  symbol: class Initializable[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe error indicates that the `Initializable` interface referenced on line [0m[1;36m71[0m[39m of [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FileSystemEmitter.java` cannot be found. This suggests either:[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The interface doesn't exist in the codebase[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The interface is in a different package and requires an import statement[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The interface name is incorrect[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Further Investigation[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo resolve the compilation error and complete the security fix, the following areas[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould be investigated:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Interface Resolution**: Search the Tika codebase for any `Initializable` [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minterface or similar lifecycle management interfaces to determine the correct [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minterface name and import path[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **FileSystemEmitter Lifecycle**: Investigate how `FileSystemEmitter` is [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minstantiated and initialized to understand if implementing an initialization [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minterface is necessary or if the validation can be performed differently[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **FilenameUtils Availability**: Verify that `[0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` used in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mAbstractEmbeddedDocumentBytesHandler.sanitizeEmbeddedPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is available and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproperly imported from Apache Commons IO[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Test Coverage**: Examine existing test files for `FileSystemEmitter` and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`AbstractEmbeddedDocumentBytesHandler` to understand expected behavior and edge [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcases[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **BasePath Initialization**: Review how `basePath` is set in `FileSystemEmitter`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto ensure the uninitialized field declaration doesn't break existing functionality[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Alternative Validation Approaches**: Investigate if other emitter [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimplementations in the codebase have similar path validation logic that could serve[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mas a reference[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **Security Test Cases**: Look for existing security-focused tests in the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodebase to understand how path traversal scenarios should be tested[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m48[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m49[0m[39m:     * Scans the given file name for reserved characters on different OSs and[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m50[0m[39m:     * file systems and returns a sanitized version of the name with the[0m         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m53[0m[39m:     * For example <code>why?.zip<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m> will be converted into [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>why%3F.zip<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m55[0m[39m:     * @param name the file name to be normalized - NOT NULL[0m                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m57[0m[39m:     * @throws IllegalArgumentException if name is null[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m58[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m59[0m[39m:    public static String [0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal String name[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m60[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mname == null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m61[0m[39m:            throw new [0m[1;35mIllegalArgumentException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"name cannot be null"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m64[0m[39m:        StringBuilder sb = new [0m[1;35mStringBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m66[0m[39m:        for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mchar c : [0m[1;35mname.toCharArray[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m67[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mRESERVED.contains[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m68[0m[39m:                [0m[1;35msb.append[0m[1;39m([0m[32m'%'[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.append[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mc < [0m[1;36m16[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ? [0m[32m"0"[0m[39m : [0m[32m""[0m[1;39m)[0m                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35m.append[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mInteger.toHexString[0m[1;39m([0m[39mc[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toUpperCase[0m[1;39m([0m[39mLocale.ROOT[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m72[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m76[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m78[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m79[0m[39m:     * This is a duplication of the algorithm and functionality[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m80[0m[39m:     * available in commons io FilenameUtils.  If Java's File were[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m81[0m[39m:     * able handle Windows file paths correctly in linux,[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m82[0m[39m:     * we wouldn't need this.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m83[0m[39m:     * <p>[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m84[0m[39m:     * The goal of this is to get a filename from a path.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m85[0m[39m:     * The package parsers and some other embedded doc[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m86[0m[39m:     * extractors could put anything into TikaCoreProperties.RESOURCE_NAME_KEY.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m87[0m[39m:     * <p>[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m88[0m[39m:     * If a careless client used that filename as if it were a[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m89[0m[39m:     * filename and not a path when writing embedded files,[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m90[0m[39m:     * bad things could happen.  Consider: [0m[32m"../../../my_ppt.ppt"[0m[39m.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m91[0m[39m:     * <p>[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m92[0m[39m:     * Consider using this in combination with [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link #[0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m93[0m[39m:     *[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m94[0m[39m:     * @param path path to strip[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m95[0m[39m:     * @return empty string or a filename, never null[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m96[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m97[0m[39m:    public static String [0m[1;35mgetName[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal String path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m98[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m99[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath == null || [0m[1;35mpath.isEmpty[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m100[0m[39m:            return StringUtils.EMPTY;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m101[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m102[0m[39m:        int unix = [0m[1;35mpath.lastIndexOf[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"/"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m103[0m[39m:        int windows = [0m[1;35mpath.lastIndexOf[0m[1;39m([0m[39m"\\"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m109[0m[39m:            return StringUtils.EMPTY;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m110[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m111[0m[39m:        return cand;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m112[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Analysis of the Evaluation Report[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe evaluation report reveals a clear compilation error: `cannot find symbol: class[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitializable` at line [0m[1;36m71[0m[39m of `FileSystemEmitter.java`. The previous patch attempted[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto declare the class as implementing `Initializable` but failed to add the required[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimport statement `org.apache.tika.config.Initializable`.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdditionally, the original security vulnerability [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath traversal attack[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m still [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mneeds to be addressed through proper path validation in the [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mFileSystemEmitter.emit[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` methods.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Core Insights from Code Snippets[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Initializable interface exists**: Found at [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`tika-core/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/config/Initializable.java`[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Requires two methods: `[0m[1;35minitialize[0m[1;39m([0m[39mMap<String, Param> params[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mcheckInitialization[0m[1;39m([0m[39mInitializableProblemHandler problemHandler[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Located in package `org.apache.tika.config`[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Reference implementations**: [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `FileSystemFetcher` implements `Initializable` and demonstrates path traversal[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidation using `[0m[1;35misDescendant[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` helper[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `S3Emitter` shows proper import statements and interface implementation [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpattern[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Both use similar validation approaches adapted to their specific use cases[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Path traversal vulnerability flow**:[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Archive entry names from `PackageParser` → [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TikaCoreProperties.RESOURCE_NAME_KEY` → `AbstractEmbeddedDocumentBytesHandler` → [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mEmittingEmbeddedDocumentBytesHandler.add[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` → `[0m[1;35mFileSystemEmitter.emit[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Current code at line [0m[1;36m147[0m[39m does `[0m[1;35mbasePath.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` without validation[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - TikaCoreProperties documentation explicitly warns against using [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRESOURCE_NAME_KEY for file paths[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Existing validation patterns**:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `[0m[1;35mFileSystemFetcher.isDescendant[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` uses [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mtoAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` pattern[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This approach works for files that don't exist yet [0m[1;39m([0m[39munlike `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Implement [0m[1;35mcheckInitialization[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Method[0m                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Rationale**: [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Validates `basePath` configuration following `FileSystemFetcher` pattern [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m156[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m181[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Warns about security risks when `basePath` is not set[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Prevents null byte injection attacks[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Uses same warning message style as `FileSystemFetcher` for consistency[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m. Add [0m[1;35misDescendant[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Helper Method[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdd the following private static method [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcan be placed before the ON_EXISTS enum[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m * Validates that the descendant path is within the root path.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m * This prevents path traversal attacks.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m *[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m * @param root the root path[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m * @param descendant the path to validate[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m * @return true if descendant is within root, false otherwise[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprivate static boolean [0m[1;35misDescendant[0m[1;39m([0m[39mPath root, Path descendant[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return [0m[1;35mdescendant.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mroot.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Rationale**: [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Copied from `[0m[1;35mFileSystemFetcher.isDescendant[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m67[0m[1;39m)[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Uses `[0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` instead of `[0m[1;35mtoRealPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` since files don't exist yet during [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39memission[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mtoAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` resolves `.` and `..` components and converts to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mabsolute path[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mstartsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` check ensures descendant is within root[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This is the core security check that prevents path traversal attacks[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m. Add Path Validation in [0m[1;35memit[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString path, InputStream[0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Method[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mModify the `[0m[1;35memit[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString path, InputStream inputStream, Metadata userMetadata, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mParseContext parseContext[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method at line [0m[1;36m145[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m165[0m[39m.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter line [0m[1;36m147[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Path target = [0m[1;35mbasePath.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, add:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Validate that the resolved path stays within basePath to prevent path traversal[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35misDescendant[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbasePath, target[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    throw new [0m[1;35mIOException[0m[1;39m([0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[32m"path must resolve to be a descendant of the 'basePath': "[0m[39m + path[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Rationale**:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This is the critical security fix that prevents the path traversal vulnerability[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Validates the resolved path BEFORE any file system operations[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Throws `IOException` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mconsistent with method signature[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m if validation fails[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Error message clearly indicates the security constraint[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Must be done after `[0m[1;35mresolve[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` but before `[0m[1;35mcreateDirectories[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or `[0m[1;35mFiles.copy[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m. Add Path Validation in [0m[1;35memit[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString emitKey, List<Metadata>[0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Method[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mModify the `[0m[1;35memit[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString emitKey, List<Metadata> metadataList, ParseContext [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparseContext[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method at lines [0m[1;36m76[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m98[0m[39m.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mChange the resolution logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m86[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m90[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m from:[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbasePath != null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    output = [0m[1;35mbasePath.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39memitKey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    output = [0m[1;35mPaths.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39memitKey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```java[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbasePath != null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    output = [0m[1;35mbasePath.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39memitKey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Validate that the resolved path stays within basePath to prevent path [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtraversal[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35misDescendant[0m[1;39m([0m[39mbasePath, output[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        throw new [0m[1;35mTikaEmitterException[0m[1;39m([0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                [0m[32m"emitKey must resolve to be a descendant of the 'basePath': "[0m[39m + [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39memitKey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    output = [0m[1;35mPaths.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39memitKey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Rationale**:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Protects the metadata emit path in addition to the stream emit path[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Uses `TikaEmitterException` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mconsistent with method signature[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Only validates when `basePath` is set [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhen null, absolute paths are allowed[0m[1;39m)[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Ensures both emit methods have the same security posture[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### [0m[1;36m9[0m[39m. Optional: Sanitize Path in AbstractEmbeddedDocumentBytesHandler [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDefense in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDepth[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe previous patch attempted to add `[0m[1;35msanitizeEmbeddedPath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`AbstractEmbeddedDocumentBytesHandler`. While not strictly necessary since [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidation in `FileSystemEmitter` is the enforcement point, this can be improved as[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefense in depth.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**However, based on the evaluation report's instruction to focus on fixing the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompilation error and the fact that the FileSystemEmitter validation is the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcritical fix, I recommend NOT reapplying the AbstractEmbeddedDocumentBytesHandler [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchanges in this patch attempt.**[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m**Rationale**:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The previous patch's use of `[0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` for path sanitization was[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minsufficient[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` only handles reserved characters, not path traversal[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The `[0m[1;35maddSubDirs[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method's current attempt at sanitization [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m102[0m[39m: [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mreplaceAll[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"\\.\\./"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"/"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is already present[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The critical fix is validation at the enforcement point [0m[1;39m([0m[39mFileSystemEmitter[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, not [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mupstream sanitization[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Removing this change simplifies the patch and focuses on the essential security [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfix[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- If upstream sanitization is desired later, it should use [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mFilenameUtils.getName[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to extract only the filename component[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## How This Fix Addresses the Issues[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Compilation Error Resolution[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds the missing `import org.apache.tika.config.Initializable;` statement[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adds all other required imports for the interface implementation[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Implements both required interface methods[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Follows the exact pattern used by `FileSystemFetcher` and `S3Emitter`[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Security Vulnerability Resolution  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Implements path traversal validation using the proven `[0m[1;35misDescendant[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` pattern[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Validates paths in both `[0m[1;35memit[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` methods before any file system operations[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Prevents malicious paths like `q/r/s/t/.[0m[35m/input.bin/../../../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m[39m` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrom escaping the base directory[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Uses `[0m[1;35mnormalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` which resolves `.` and `..` components to catch all traversal [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatterns[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Preservation of Existing Logic[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Does not modify any existing functionality[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Only adds validation checks that reject invalid inputs[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Maintains the same behavior for valid paths[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Does not change the `basePath` initialization [0m[1;39m([0m[39mkeeps `= null`[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Does not modify the `ON_EXISTS` enum or file copying logic[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Does not modify any other emitter or fetcher code[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Does not modify fuzzing harness or test code[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Potential Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Strict path validation may reject previously accepted paths**: [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Effect**: Paths that previously [0m[32m"worked"[0m[39m through accidental traversal will [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnow be rejected[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: This is the intended security behavior; the previous behavior [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwas a vulnerability[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Impact**: Legitimate use cases should use proper relative paths within [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbasePath[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **basePath must be set for security**:[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Effect**: Warning logged if basePath is not configured[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: The warning is informational; system still functions but with [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreduced security[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Impact**: Users should configure basePath in production environments[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Performance overhead from path normalization**:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Effect**: Each emit operation performs path normalization[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: Normalization is lightweight and necessary for security[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Impact**: Negligible performance impact compared to file I/O operations[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## References to Similar Solutions in Codebase[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **FileSystemFetcher** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m67[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m79[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m82[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m156[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m181[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Demonstrates [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35misDescendant[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` pattern and `Initializable` implementation[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **S3Emitter** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m99[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m295[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m329[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Shows proper `Initializable` interface [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimplementation for emitters[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **[0m[1;35mFSUtil.resolveRelative[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m197[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m202[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Shows additional absolute path [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecking pattern[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **TikaCoreProperties documentation** [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m58[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m62[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m80[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m82[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: Explicitly warns [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39magainst using RESOURCE_NAME_KEY for file paths[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis fix strategy provides a complete, focused solution that resolves both the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompilation error and the security vulnerability while maintaining compatibility [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith existing functionality.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
